Quick Tips

So that's the hard bit done! And the good news is there are strategies to help you manage stress. Take a look below and check the box for the ones you already do - how'd you go?

Talk it out

You won't be the only person who's been through it. Share with a friend, family member or someone you trust. Find out what they think.

Me time

We all need space to do the things we love. It gives our minds a break from humdrum, stress and busyness. It helps recharge our batteries, so schedule it in and make it part of your routine.

Switch off

Practice mindfulness. Be still and take mini-breaks. Get up, stretch, walk around the block. Learn how to breathe properly - and give meditation a go (sounds a bit 'new age' we know, but trust us, it works!)

Feed the engine

We are what we eat/drink so make smart choices about what you put in your mouth and when! Drink as much water as possible. Have a treat now and again. Be in tune and listen to your body.

Get physical

Exercise helps us feel better about ourselves. It releases the endorphins we need to feel emotionally stable. Plus it helps us sleep (zzzz).
